        "body" : "Example of such handler should be provided. This is what I normally user as the handler:\r\n\r\n```\r\n- name: Clean YUM cache\r\n  shell: env yum clean all\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `env` is there to prevent Ansible from displaying warning that the `yum` module should be used instead. The same can be used for `service` commands (e.g `env service postgresql init`).",
